Assuming you want to protect your own service, here are several common approaches. Tell me your stack and I can tailor it precisely.

1) Nginx: deny all or restrict by IP
- Deny everyone:
  server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;
    return 403;
  }

- Allow only a whitelist of IPs:
  server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;

    location / {
      allow 203.0.113.10;
      allow 198.51.100.23;
      deny all;
    }
  }

- Maintenance mode (serve a static page, deny others):
  server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;

    if ($remote_addr !~ ^(203\.0\.113\.10|198\.51\.100\.23)$) {
      return 503;
    }
    location = /maintenance.html { root /var/www/html; }
    error_page 503 /maintenance.html;
  }

2) Apache (httpd): deny all or restrict by IP
- Deny everyone:
  <VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName example.com
    <Location />
      Require all denied
    </Location>
  </VirtualHost>

- Allow only specific IPs:
  <VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName example.com
    <Location />
      Require ip 203.0.113.10
      Require ip 198.51.100.23
      Require all denied
    </Location>
  </VirtualHost>

- Maintenance mode:
  <VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName example.com
    RewriteEngine On
    RewriteCond %{REMOTE_ADDR} !^(203\.0\.113\.10|198\.51\.100\.23)$
    RewriteRule ^ - [R=503,L]
    ErrorDocument 503 /maintenance.html
    Alias /maintenance.html /var/www/html/maintenance.html
  </VirtualHost>

3) Cloudflare (WAF rules)
- Block all except your IPs:
  - Create a Firewall Rule: (ip.src not in {203.0.113.10 198.51.100.23}) then Block or Serve 403.
- Country/geolocation block:
  - Rule: (ip.geoip.country in {"CN" "RU"}) then Block.
- Rate limiting:
  - Configure rules to throttle excessive requests.

4) Application-level middleware (Node.js Express)
- Deny all:
  const express = require('express');
  const app = express();
  app.use((req, res) => res.status(403).send('Access denied'));
  app.listen(3000);

- Allow only whitelist:
  const whitelist = new Set(['203.0.113.10', '198.51.100.23']);
  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    if (whitelist.has(req.ip)) return next();
    res.status(403).send('Access denied');
  });

- Maintenance mode toggle via env:
  const MAINTENANCE = process.env.MAINTENANCE === 'true';
  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    if (MAINTENANCE) return res.status(503).send('Service temporarily unavailable');
    next();
  });

5) Linux firewall (iptables/nftables) to block at the network edge
- iptables: block all incoming to port 80/443 except whitelisted IPs:
