  iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 443 -s 203.0.113.10 -j ACCEPT
  iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 443 -s 198.51.100.23 -j ACCEPT
  iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 443 -j DROP

6) IIS (Windows)
- Use IP and Domain Restrictions feature:
  - Add Deny Entry for all (*) and then Add Allow Entry for specific IPs.
- Web.config to deny all:
