    <security>
      <ipSecurity allowUnlisted="false">
      </ipSecurity>
    </security>
  </system.webServer>

7) OAuth/authentication requirement
- Require login before access; unauthenticated requests return 401/403. Implement via reverse proxy (e.g., oauth2-proxy with Nginx/Traefik) or app middleware.

8) Robots and polite blocking
- If you want to block crawlers, set robots.txt: User-agent: * Disallow: /
- Combine with server-side checks and rate-limiting; robots.txt is voluntary.

Best practices:
- Prefer deny-by-default with explicit allow for sensitive services (admin panels).
- Log denied requests for auditing.
- Return appropriate status codes (403 Forbidden, 401 Unauthorized, 503 Service Unavailable).
- Test rules carefully to avoid locking yourself out. Keep a backdoor IP or console access.
- Document changes and maintain a rollback plan.

